tle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/19/01 4:45:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13530.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing L Guk</span><hr size=1> What about breaking Magi room?  Use Pacify on them?  How hard is th magi to solo, been a while since I fought him.  I guess key to taking him down is just proper stuning?<br><br>Thanks for the info <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uakronn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Akronn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/19/01 5:04:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13530.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing L Guk</span><hr size=1> I soloed the area from May to November this year so I might be considered an expert! A few points:<br><br>1.) Don't aggro the Dar as mentioned above. Even at 57 I couldn't single pull him unless he was a bit away from the Lord room. He will bring friends!<br><br>2.) No tricks needed to single pull the two AM spawns. You can peek around the corner a bit and the one nearest you will aggro. I think just once in about a thousand times I accidentially aggroed both. No big deal, just root them and camp.<br><br>3.) For pulling everything else, well the usual rules apply. I would go IU, run until I saw a blue and either attack it to pull if the way back was clear or root it and go IU to head back to camp. I hardly ever used stun or a dd to pull. Just not necessary.<br><br>4.) If there happens to be an AM group already, just leave. There really aren't enough spawns for the both of you and this is how accidents happen. Lord always gets pulled, his posse is always running around, and frequently you'll get caught with a couple of adds at the wrong time. Every time I've died, it's been because of the AM group.<br><br>5.) If you die, good luck finding a rez. In peak times there's frequently only 12 people in all of Guk. Have a pocket cleric handy.<br><br>6.) I hate to say this... but it's really really boring! Don't go down there thinking you'll be making mad exp, cause you won't. It is steady and not all that bad... but EQ is a social game and your guildchat better be entertaining or you'll go insane.<br><br>I had to solo in Guk because my job at the time wouldn't allow me to play very long in the evenings. I was working a TON of hours and frequently only had an hour or two to kill at a time. I missed out on alot of fun and wished things were different, but alas it was doomed to be just me and the froggies! <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showMessage?topicID=13514.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showMessage?topicID=13464.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13530.topic&index=3><img src=http://eq1.castersrealm.com/pon/images/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.emailToFriend?topicID=13530.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.threadControl?topicID=13530.to